Real Madrid has confirmed that the club has agreed on a transfer deal for defender, Javi Sanchez, to join Real Valladolid. Zinedine Zidane’s side disclosed this in a statement on their official website on Tuesday. “Real Madrid CF and Real Valladolid CF have agreed to transfer the player Javi Sánchez,” the statement read. “The club wants to thank Javi Sánchez for all these years of dedication, professionalism and exemplary behaviour since, at the age of 8, he came to our academy in 2005, and wishes him good luck in his new stage.” Sanchez was promoted to Real Madrid’s senior team in 2018. The 23-year-old was loaned to Valladolid in 2019 after making just one appearance for the Los Blancos.